AlamoneWaryLines		1	$ 33	$ Well, scram! $
AlamoneWaryLines		2	$ 68	$ And you best not have touched anything! $

AlamonePardonID 6
AlamonePardonLines		0	$ 39	$ Hrm... $
AlamonePardonLines		1	$ 59	$ Seems you didn't touch anything. $
AlamonePardonLines		2	$ 68	$ Don't make me suspect you again, you hear? $

AlamoneAccusationID 7
AlamoneAccusationLines		0	$ 27	$ Thief! $
AlamoneAccusationLines		1	$ 57	$ What the hell is wrong with you? $
AlamoneAccusationLines		2	$ 89	$ And what, you think you're just gonna show up to shop again? $
AlamoneAccusationLines		3	$ 23	$ Ha! $
AlamoneAccusationLines		4	$ 122	$ If you want to legitimately buy my stuff, you better be willing to pay for your crime! $

AlamoneUndeadRuleID 8
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		0	$ 59	$ Agh, those undead monsters... $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		1	$ 79	$ Used to be that undead were only told of in history and war stories. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		2	$ 66	$ Never saw any myself, none of us did, not until HE came. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		3	$ 92	$ Most people fled this area when the siege ended, so not many reapers came this way. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		4	$ 84	$ Then, amidst the hiding and skirmishing on the streets... $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		5	$ 57	$ Well, anyways, he gave us reason to hate him. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		6	$ 82	$ Many people I knew died, a few became reapers, but most... $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		7	$ 38	$ Most of them, he broke. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		8	$ 67	$ I'm not hiding in here from reapers, they don't scare me. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		9	$ 47	$ I've held out this long, haven't I? $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		10	$ 39	$ They'll never get to me. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		11	$ 79	$ But... It's a bit different when it's your old friends. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		12	$ 103	$ Sometimes the screaming in the distance makes me regret living... Surviving. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		13	$ 32	$ But I can't die. $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		14	$ 77	$ Too many lost or dead for us, for me to get this far... $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		15	$ 27	$ I can't- It- $
AlamoneUndeadRuleLines		16	$ 37	$ It wasn't all in vain. $

AlamoneDepthsID 9
AlamoneDepthsLines		0	$ 100	$ Years ago, before my time, some people in Ixinik weren't happy with the way things were done. $
AlamoneDepthsLines		1	$ 71	$ They started a revolution, lost, and got exiled down below. $
AlamoneDepthsLines		2	$ 103	$ Since then, people've found a fair few revolutionaries hiding in our midst, waiting, plotting. $
AlamoneDepthsLines		3	$ 79	$ They all get shipped down to the depths, where they rightly belong. $
AlamoneDepthsLines		4	$ 83	$ Pay no attention to such filth, unless they try and eat you or something. $
AlamoneDepthsLines		5	$ 79	$ They're probably the cause of this whole reaping... $
AlamoneDepthsLines		6	$ 51	$ We should've just hung the whole lot. $

AlamoneAnythingElseID 10
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	0	$ 22	$ Oh! $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	1	$ 36	$ Yes, glad you asked. $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	2	$ 114	$ Awhile back... Well, yesterday, but that's not a very helpful measure of time... $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	3	$ 72	$ A man came through here, called himself Gjeldar the 'Cursed'. $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	4	$ 86	$ Cursed with what beats me, but even if a warrior, he's still just a normal man. $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	5	$ 54	$ Not like, um, well... Sorry. $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	6	$ 53	$ You'll keep an eye out for him, won't you? $
AlamoneAnythingElseLines	7	$ 55	$ I fear death may have already found him. $

AlamoneNewProphetID 11
AlamoneNewProphetLines		0	$ 30	$ Ah, you're- $
AlamoneNewProphetLines		1	$ 50	$ Wait, did you...? $
AlamoneNewProphetLines		2	$ 35	$ ... $
AlamoneNewProphetLines		3	$ 54	$ You can't fool me, §ltraitor§b§o. $
AlamoneNewProphetLines		4	$ 29	$ GET OUT! $
AlamoneNewProphetLines		5	$ 42	$ GET OUT OF MY HOUSE! $

